HEADWORD: Necrotomy
<hw>Nec*rot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>nekro`s</grk> dead person + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The dissection of dead bodies; also, excision of
necrosed bone.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Nec`ro*tom"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> -- <wf>Nec*rot"o*mist</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
